We welcome more contributors join us. Here are some of channels we use to communicate and contribute. Mailing list: chubaofs-maintainers@groups.io – discussion around ChubaoFS usage, community support and developer discussion. Slack: chubaofs.slack.com Twitter: @ChubaoFS Issue tracker: Use the Github issue tracker to file bugs and features request. If you need support, please send your questions to the chubaofs-maintainers@groups.io mailing list rather than filing a GitHub issue. Contributing We welcome community contributions! If you are planning on making more elaborate or controversial changes, please discuss them on the mailing list or on GitHub before sending a pull request. Project Governance ChubaoFS is an independent open-source project and not controlled by any single company. More details please refer to Governance.md. Code of Conduct To make ChubaoFS a welcoming and harassment-free experience for everyone, we follow the CNCF Code of Conduct. Docs Blog Community ©2019 The ChubaoFS Authors

posts.title: ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019
posts.slug: 2019-09-10 ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019
posts.path: 2019/09/10/2019-09-10 ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019/
posts.permalink: http://chubao.io/2019/09/10/2019-09-10 ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019/
posts.excerpt: ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019As the invitation from Intel, our speaker sharing the main architecture design of ChubaoFS and the key features.
posts.text: ChubaoFS talk at Intel IPDC summit 2019As the invitation from Intel, our speaker sharing the main architecture design of ChubaoFS and the key features. High performance: Optimized for both large and small files. Multi-Tenancy: Share the whole storage and resource utilization ratio. General- Purpose Storage Engine: Support both sequential and random read/write. Highly Scalable: Individual meta and data node clusters. Scales with meta and data partitions increase. POSIX filesystem APIs: Complaint whenever possible, and compromise between semantics and performance. Meanwhile ChubaoFS user scenarios were shared and increasing number of people interested in these. Underlying storage for in-memory DB: Preserve snapshots. Cloud storage for AI platform Training service: Decouple computing from storage. Latency-sensitive services: Used for storing Nginx logs. Elasticsearch: Takes care of replications and high availability. Service MySQL: Running MySQL history tables on ChubaoFS directly since most of the requests are read.

posts.text: CNCF Storage SIG Propose ChubaoFS to SandboxAs we presented the ChubaoFS project on Jun 12th CNCF Storage SIG meeting, today we really excited to get the feedback back from storage SIG, and they are happy to propose this project to Sandbox. Recording for the session is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l0-cUTPcpaQ ChubaoFS consists of a metadata subsystem, a data subsystem, and a resource manager, and can be accessed by different clients (as a set of application processes) hosted on the containers through different file system instances called volumes. The metadata subsystem stores the file metadata, and consists of a set of meta nodes. Each meta node consists of a set of meta partitions. The ChubaoFS questionnaire docs: https://docs.google.com/document/d/15Cnz3AHooqtml0xWhF6Hgei4gpWiRJbwoVCO_pN2z4c/edit?usp=sharing

posts.title: ChubaoFS gave a talk on Hackathon
posts.slug: 2019-04-20 ChubaoFS gave a talk on Hackathon
posts.path: 2019/04/20/2019-04-20 ChubaoFS gave a talk on Hackathon/
posts.permalink: http://chubao.io/2019/04/20/2019-04-20 ChubaoFS gave a talk on Hackathon/
posts.excerpt: ChubaoFS gave a talk on HackathonChubaoFS gave a talk “CFS, native for large-scale container service platform of distributed file system” on the 9th China Open Source Hackathon.
posts.text: ChubaoFS gave a talk on HackathonChubaoFS gave a talk “CFS, native for large-scale container service platform of distributed file system” on the 9th China Open Source Hackathon. ChubaoFS (Chubao File System, or CFS for short) is a distributed file system. It provides files system for upper-layer applications. The system POSIX interface has the characteristics: High availability, High scalability, Multi-tenancy, Easy operation and maintenance. The original aim of the design is to provide a persistent storage solution for JD’s huge container clusters, while it also can be used as a general cloud storage for the business side. After more than half a year of stable online operation, it services more than 30 business applications. Business scenarios are not limited to backup storage of massive data, also included MySQL underlying storage (history table), Elastic search underlying storage, Hbase backend storage, AI platform model training backend storage, etc. At the same time, the design of CFS has its own unique characteristics, and the paper about the design has been accepted by SIGMOD2019 conference.

posts.excerpt: ChubaoFS First Release is ComingChubaoFS (ChubaoFS file system, or CFS) is a distributed file system for cloud native applications. It is designed to provide persistent storage solution for container cluster and also be used as general cloud storage for business parties.
posts.text: ChubaoFS First Release is ComingChubaoFS (ChubaoFS file system, or CFS) is a distributed file system for cloud native applications. It is designed to provide persistent storage solution for container cluster and also be used as general cloud storage for business parties. The first release version has been published on Github: https://github.com/chubaofs/chubaofs/releases/tag/v1.0.0 The key features are included: High performance for both large files and small files General purpose storage engine Multi-tenancy POSIX-compliant APIs High scalability with separated metadata cluster
